description: Cerro de Pasco Resources Inc., a natural resource company, engages in the acquisition, exploration, and development of mineral properties. The company primarily explores for zinc, lead, and silver deposits. It holds 100% interests in the El Metalurgista mining concession covering an area of approximately 95.74 hectares located in Lima, Peru. The company was founded in 2012 and is headquartered in Saint-Sauveur, Canada.
